quran[53]{c,v,t}:
  51,31,"He (Abraham) said: \"Then (after that), what is your concern, O you (heavenly) envoys"
  51,32,"They said: \"Indeed, we have been sent to a people who are all criminals"
  51,33,So that We may send upon them stones of baked clay
  51,34,Marked out in your Lord’s Presence for (the destruction of) the people wasteful (of their God-given faculties and) committing excesses
  51,35,We brought out (from the land) those in it who were believers
  51,36,But We did not find there any but a single house of Muslims (those wholly submitted to God)
  51,37,We left there a clear sign (of the truth of God’s Messages) for those who fear the painful punishment
  51,38,"And in (the exemplary history of) Moses too (there is a clear sign): We sent him as Messenger to the Pharaoh with an evident authority"
  51,39,"But the Pharaoh turned away (from Our Message), together with his hosts, and said: \"(Moses is either) a sorcerer or a madman"
  51,40,"So We seized him and his hosts, and hurled them into the sea. And he was self-accused, remorseful (too late, when he was drowning)"
  51,41,"And in (the exemplary history of the tribe of) ‘Ad also (there is a clear sign), when We sent upon them the devastating wind"
  51,42,"It spared nothing that it reached, but made it like ashes"
  51,43,"And in (the exemplary history of the tribe of) Thamud also (there is a clear sign), when they (were given respite and) it was said to them: \"Enjoy life for a little while"
  51,44,"But they rebelled against their Lord’s decree, so the thunderbolt (along with the blast) seized them, even while they were looking on"
  51,45,"They were not able to rise up (still less escape the punishment), nor were able to receive help"
  51,46,(And We had destroyed) the people of Noah before. They were a people transgressing (God’s bounds)
  51,47,"And the heaven, We have constructed it mightily, and it is surely We Who have vast power, and keep expanding it"
  51,48,"And the earth, We have spread it out, and how excellent We are in spreading it out (like a cradle)"
  51,49,"And all things We have created in pairs, so that you may reflect and be mindful"
  51,50,"So, flee to (refuge in) God. I am surely from Him to you a plain warner"
  51,51,And do not set up another deity besides God. I am surely a plain warner from Him to you
  51,52,"Similarly, no Messenger came to the peoples who lived before them but they said of him (in like manner): \"A sorcerer or a madman"
  51,53,Have they bequeathed this to one another (by way of response)? They were indeed a rebellious people
  51,54,"So, turn away from disputing with them, and you are not to be blamed (for doing so)"
  51,55,"But remind and warn, for reminding and warning are of benefit to the believers"
  51,56,I have not created the jinn and humankind but to (know and) worship Me (exclusively)
  51,57,"I demand of them no provision, nor do I demand that they should feed Me"
  51,58,"Surely God – it is He Who is the All-Providing, Lord of all might, and the All-Forceful"
  51,59,"So surely those who commit the greatest wrong (namely, not believing in and worshipping God or associating partners with Him in worship), will have their share (of the punishment) like the share of their fellows (of old who were destroyed). Then, let them not ask Me to hasten it"
  51,60,"Then, woe to those who disbelieve because of their Day with which they are threatened"
  52,1,By the Mount (Sinai)
  52,2,And by a Book inscribed
  52,3,In parchments outstretched
  52,4,And by Bayt al-Ma‘mur (the House continuously frequented)
  52,5,And by the canopy (of heaven) raised high
  52,6,And by the sea kept filled (and ready to overflow)
  52,7,The punishment of your Lord will certainly take place
  52,8,There is none that can avert it
  52,9,On that Day the heaven will be convulsed violently
  52,10,And the mountains will move away with an awesome movement
  52,11,"Woe, then, on that Day to those who deny (God’s Message and the Messengers) –"
  52,12,"Those who are habitually playing, absorbed (in vanities)"
  52,13,On that Day they will be forcefully thrust into the fire of Hell
  52,14,This is the Fire which you used to deny
  52,15,"Is this sorcery (for you used to deride the Revelation as sorcery), or is it that you do not see (so that, for you, it is something illusory)"
  52,16,"Suffer the heat of it now! Bear it patiently, or do not bear it patiently, it is all the same to you. You are only being recompensed for all that you used to do (in the world)"
  52,17,"The God-revering, pious ones will surely be in Gardens and bliss"
  52,18,Enjoying all that their Lord will grant them (by His grace and in recompense for their good deeds); and their Lord has protected them from the punishment of the Blazing Flame
  52,19,Eat and drink to your hearts’ content for all that you used to do (in the world)
  52,20,"They will recline on thrones arranged; and We have assigned for them maidens pure, beautiful of eye"
  52,21,"Those who have believed and their offspring have followed them in faith, We will unite them with their offspring (even though the faith of the latter may not be of the same degree as that of the former), and We will not decrease the reward of their deeds in anything (because of their being united with their offspring). Every person will enjoy according to what he has earned"
  52,22,"And We will provide them with fruit and meat, one meal after the other, such as they desire"
  52,23,"There they will pass among one another a cup wherein is (a drink inciting) no false, foolish talk nor sin"